# 🔗 AWS Serverless URL Shortener

A **Serverless URL Shortener** built using Amazon Web Services.
This project converts long URLs into short links with optional custom aliases and tracks click analytics.

The system is built using a **fully serverless architecture**, meaning no servers need to be managed.

---

# 🚀 Features

* 🔗 Shorten long URLs instantly
* 📝 Custom alias support (example: `/hotstar`)
* 📊 Click analytics (track how many times a link is opened)
* ⚡ Fully serverless architecture
* 🌐 Frontend hosted on S3
* 📈 Monitoring with CloudWatch

---

# 🏗️ Architecture

```
User
  ↓
Frontend (Amazon S3)
  ↓
Amazon API Gateway
  ↓
AWS Lambda (Shorten Function)
  ↓
Amazon DynamoDB
```

Redirect Flow:

```
User opens short URL
        ↓
Amazon API Gateway
        ↓
AWS Lambda (Redirect Function)
        ↓
Amazon DynamoDB lookup
        ↓
Redirect to original URL
```

---

# 🧰 AWS Services Used

| Service            | Purpose                                 |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| Amazon S3          | Hosts the frontend website              |
| Amazon API Gateway | Exposes REST API endpoints              |
| AWS Lambda         | Backend logic for shortening & redirect |
| Amazon DynamoDB    | Stores URL mappings                     |
| Amazon CloudWatch  | Logs and monitoring                     |

---

# ⚙️ Lambda Functions

Two Lambda functions are used in this architecture.

### 1️⃣ URL Shortening Function

Function name:

```
url-shortener-shorten
```

Responsibilities:

* Accept long URL
* Generate short code
* Store mapping in DynamoDB
* Return short URL

API Endpoint:

```
POST /shorten
```

---

### 2️⃣ URL Redirect Function

Function name:

```
url-shortener-redirect
```

Responsibilities:

* Receive short code
* Fetch original URL from DynamoDB
* Increment click counter
* Redirect user

API Endpoint:

```
GET /{short_code}
```

---

# 📊 DynamoDB Table

Table name:

```
url-mappings
```

Primary key:

```
short_code (String)
```

Example record:

| short_code | long_url            | clicks |
| ---------- | ------------------- | ------ |
| hotstar    | https://hotstar.com | 12     |
| netflix    | https://netflix.com | 7      |

---

# 🌐 Frontend

The frontend is a simple HTML interface hosted using **Amazon S3 Static Website Hosting**.

Users can:

* Enter a long URL
* Add an optional custom alias
* Generate a short link

Example result:

```
https://<api-id>.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/hotstar
```

---

# 📈 Monitoring

Application logs and metrics are monitored using **Amazon CloudWatch**.

Tracked metrics include:

* Lambda execution logs
* API Gateway request logs
* Error tracking

A CloudWatch dashboard was also created to monitor **EC2 CPU Utilization** as part of infrastructure monitoring practice.

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```
aws-serverless-url-shortener
│
├── index.html
├── lambda
│   ├── shorten.py
│   └── redirect.py
├── README.md
└── screenshots
```

---

# 🧪 Example Usage

Input:

```
https://google.com
```

Output:

```
https://<api-id>.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/google
```

Opening the short link redirects the user to the original URL.

